126. Erqo vides quam Grande] “ So you see what a return for his sufferings the death of one Mycenaean damsel won.'' He supposes him to have had a ‘ nubilis Iphigenia,' and to have sacrificed her, and to have had his trouble soothed by the fruits of his devotion in the old man’s will.
